Explanation:
index.html: Sets up the basic visual structure of the game with a title, instructions, input field, button, and message area.
style.css: Provides basic styling for the game elements to improve user experience.
script.js: Handles the game logic:
Generates a random target number.
Tracks the number of attempts.
Listens for the button click event.
Validates the user's guess.
Provides feedback based on the guess (too low, too high, or correct).
Enables or disables the guess button based on the game state.

Running the Game:
Save the code as index.html, style.css, and script.js in the same directory.
Open index.html in a web browser to start playing.

Additional Features (Optional):
Add a difficulty level that changes the range of the target number or the number of allowed guesses.
Display a history of previous guesses and attempts.
Implement a leaderboard to track high scores.
